where $J_{i}$ is the current density of the collector current of the $i^{\text {th }}$ transistor, and $J_{i 0}$ is the same density at the reference temperature.

Now, assume the difference between two base-emitter voltages is multiplied by a factor K and added to the base-emitter voltage of the junction with the higher current density. Using (7.16) and (7.19) along with (7.14), we obtain

$$
\begin{align*}
