#### EXAMPLE 7.4

Estimate the temperature dependence at $0^{\circ} \mathrm{C}$ for a bandgap voltage reference designed to have zero temperature dependence at $20^{\circ} \mathrm{C}$. Present the result as $\mathrm{ppm} / \mathrm{K}$.

#### Solution

Recalling that $0^{\circ} \mathrm{K}$ corresponds to $-273^{\circ} \mathrm{C}$, we can write $\mathrm{T}_{0}=293 \mathrm{~K}$ and $\mathrm{T}=273 \mathrm{~K}$. Substituting these values into (7.27), we get

$$
\begin{equation*}
