$$
\begin{equation*}
\frac{J_{i}}{J_{i 0}}=\frac{T}{T_{0}} \tag{7.19}
\end{equation*}
$$

where $J_{i}$ is the current density of the $i^{\text {th }}$ transistor's collector current, and $J_{i 0}$ is the density at $T_{0}$.

Next, assume the voltage difference between two base-emitter voltages is multiplied by K and added to the voltage of the junction with the higher current density. Using (7.16) and (7.19) along with (7.14), we get:

$$
