at $300{ }^{\circ} \mathrm{K}$. The name "bandgap voltage" becomes clear now. Specifically, for zero temperature dependence, the reference output is the bandgap voltage plus a small correction term for second-order effects.

The reference voltage for temperatures other than the reference is found by backsubstituting (7.22) and (7.23) into (7.20). After some manipulation, we get:

$$
